New Records: The Kings set a season-high with 38 assists on their 50 made field goals.
Key Match Events: The Kings shot 15-of-28 (53.6 percent) from beyond the arc, and 70 percent on their two-point attempts.
Post-Match Reflections: The win came just in time for the Kings as things were getting dark in Sacramento.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Kings have the second-highest two-point percentage in the league, and the offense was too good and filled with shooters to struggle for long.
Others: Next up for the Kings: 7:00 pm PT, Friday, November 15th vs. Minnesota Timberwolves
